The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Lagos State Sector Command, said on Tuesday it arrested and prosecuted 507 motorists for traffic offences from July 15 to November 20. <img class=" wp-image-1263676" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/FRSC.jpg?resize=640%2C358&#038;ssl=1" alt="Insecurity: How false alarm led FRSC personnel into Armed Robbers" width="640" height="358" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/FRSC.jpg?resize=300%2C168&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/FRSC.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/FRSC.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/FRSC.jpg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/FRSC.jpg?resize=560%2C314&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The state Sector Commander of FRSC, Mr Hyginus Omeje, disclosed this in a statement issued by the sector’s Public Education Officer, Olabisi Sonusi, in Lagos. Omeje said the traffic offenders were prosecuted at the Lagos State Special Offences (Mobile) Court. According to him, 452 of the 507 motorists were convicted by the mobile court. The sector commander said 44 were discharged and cautioned to be safety conscious while 11 had their cases adjourned. “The drivers were arrested for various offences such as driving with expired vehicle papers, lack of valid driver’s licence,  tyre rules violation, dangerous driving, overloading and number plate rule violation,” he said. Omeje said the mobile court became necessary to checkmate the excesses of drivers on the highways, adding that it would create a safer motoring environment. The sector commander advised motorists to obey traffic rules and regulations in the state. (NAN)  Vanguard The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) on Sunday said it had prosecuted 10 truck drivers for driving unlatched articulated vehicles on Lagos highways during the month. July 16, 2017 In "News" The Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC) on Thursday said two persons lost their lives in seven road crashes during the Salah holiday in Lagos. September 15, 2016 In "News" LAGOS—Federal Road Safety Commission, FRSC, Lagos sector command, in collaboration with the Lagos State Government will soon establish a joint patrol team aimed at ensuring free flow of traffic and ensure compliance with the state’s road traffic laws. November 24, 2015 In "News"